alwissenschaft. Die einzelnen Beiträge markieren aus unterschiedlichen Perspektiven das Interesse von Theologie an "Gelebter Religion". Abgeleitet wird daraus die Bedeutung der Phänomenologie für die Konstitution der Praktischen Theologie.  aIn a dialogue with philosophical phenomenology, philosophy and sociology of religion this interdisciplinary collection of articles tries to investigate the relevance of scientific endeavour into lifeworld for Systematic as well as for Practical Theology. From various perspectives the particular contributions outline the interest of theology in “living religion”. This leads to a new approach developing Practical Theology on the basis of phenomenology.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aPhenomenological theology. 0aPhilosophical theology. 0aReligion and sociology. 4aAufsatzsammlung. 4aPraktische Theologie. 4aReligionsphänomenologie. 4aTheologie. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh1 aBukow, Wolf-Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeuser, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFailing, Wolf-Eckart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFailing, Wolf-Eckart, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeimbrock, Hans-Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeimbrock, Hans-Günter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLotz, Thomas A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLotz, Thomas Α., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoxter, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider-Quindeau, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators